    {
      "id": "bkHC",
      "code_hash": "d3f4803b033bcdfe6cfb770053b29b61",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"encoderwrapper\"><code>EncoderWrapper</code></h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Wraps a VQModel encoder + quant_conv into a single <code>nn.Module</code> that:</span>\n<ol>\n<li>Runs the encoder to produce a <code>(B, 8, 4, 4)</code> feature map.</li>\n<li>Runs <code>quant_conv</code> on that map.</li>\n<li>Flattens to a <code>(B, 128)</code> vector.</li>\n</ol>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The 4\u00d74\u00d78 = 128-dimensional flat vector is the board embedding fed to the fusion head.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "lEQa",
      "code_hash": "5f645a630bcd62197ee905ae5d7161cb",
      "outputs": [],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "PKri",
      "code_hash": "f32ded628db485ad5704032c71f8b26f",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"fusionmlp\"><code>FusionMLP</code></h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The 3-layer MLP that maps the 512-dim fused vector to a scalar energy.</span>\n<h3 id=\"4-way-fusion\">4-way fusion</h3>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Given online embedding <code>ep</code> and target embedding <code>et</code>, both <code>(B, 128)</code>:</span>\n<div class=\"language-scdoc codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>fused = cat([ep, et, ep - et, ep * et])   \u2192  (B, 512)\n</code></pre></div>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The difference <code>ep \u2212 et</code> and element-wise product <code>ep \u2299 et</code> give the head\nexplicit <em>compare</em> signals, so it doesn't need to learn subtraction/multiplication\nfrom scratch inside the MLP.</span>\n<h3 id=\"mlp\">MLP</h3>\n<div class=\"language-cbmbas codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"mf\">512</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">\u2192</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LayerNorm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">\u2192</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Linear</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">512</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">256</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">\u2192</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GELU</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"err\">\u2192</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LayerNorm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">\u2192</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Linear</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">256</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">128</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">\u2192</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">GELU</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"err\">\u2192</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LayerNorm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">\u2192</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Linear</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mf\">128</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"mf\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The output is an <strong>unbounded scalar</strong> \u2014 no sigmoid/tanh \u2014 so the margin ranking\nloss can push energies apart freely.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "Xref",
      "code_hash": "2e16b4e5ab452e0df1b55c11425cdda8",
